his logarithmic power is an\n$\\varepsilon$-perturbation of the expected optimal one. The proof combines a\nrefinement of Cuculescu's construction with a quantum probabilistic\ninterpretation of de Guzm\\'an's argument. The commutative form of our argument\ngives the simplest known proof of this classical inequality. A few interesting\nconsequences are derived for Cuculescu's projections.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 Oct 2019 13:23:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-24"}
